    "kind": "task",
    "content": "Summary: Added an admin-only account filter to the routes table so admins can filter routes by owner name, while keeping the existing Latest/A-Z sort. The selected owner filter persists in localStorage per signed-in admin and resets safely when invalid or cleared. Route workspace now passes current user identity into the table, and the filter logic was isolated into a small preferences helper.\n\nTasks:\n1. [ongoing] Monitor for follow-up UI tweaks if admins want the current account option labeled differently, such as 'My account' versus the display name.\n\nAffected files:\n1. [modified] C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\RouteGate\\frontend\\src\\features\\routes\\RouteTable.tsx — Added admin-only owner filtering, persisted selection wiring, and empty-state clearing behavior in the routes table UI. | Notes: Also now accepts current user identity props from the workspace.\n2. [modified] C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\RouteGate\\frontend\\src\\features\\routes\\RoutesWorkspace.tsx — Passed current user identity to the route table so filter persistence can be scoped per signed-in user and account labels can be rendered. | Notes: No backend changes were required.\n3. [created] C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\RouteGate\\frontend\\src\\features\\routes\\routeTablePreferences.ts — Centralized localStorage keying and read/write helpers for the persisted account filter preference. | Notes: Keeps storage access out of the main table component.\n\nMemory links:\nGraph group: 1b006fa8-d33e-4fd8-9b5e-11b20eaeaaa7\nRoot memory: 1b006fa8-d33e-4fd8-9b5e-11b20eaeaaa7\nParent memories: 5a54e627-5c31-4883-8748-0490fa35ef01\nRelated memories: none",
